data.enText: two or more lines that are parallel to each other are the same distance apart at every point
parallel lines
The road and the canal are parallel to each other.

data.chText: 极相似的；同时发生的；相应的；对应的
data.enText: very similar or taking place at the same time
a parallel case
parallel trends
involving several computer operations at the same time
parallel processing
The road and the canal run parallel to each other.
The plane flew parallel to the coast.

data.chText: （尤指不同地点或时间的）极其相似的人（或情况、事件等）
data.enText: a person, a situation, an event, etc. that is very similar to another, especially one in a different place or time

data.chText: 这些观念在弗洛伊德的思想中也有极相似之处。
data.enText: These ideas have parallels in Freud's thought too.

data.chText: 这是现代无可比拟的成就。
data.enText: This is an achievement without parallel in modern times.

data.chText: 这种传统在我们的文化中是没有的。
data.enText: This tradition has no parallel in our culture.
similar features

data.chText: 20世纪60年代和90年代后期存在着有趣的相似之处。
data.enText: There are interesting parallels between the 1960s and the late 1990s.

data.chText: 在他们的经历和我们的经历之间找到相似点是可能的。
data.enText: It is possible to draw a parallel between (= find similar features in) their experience and ours.
parallel of latitude
an imaginary line around the earth that is always the same distance from the equator ; this line on a map
the 49th parallel
in parallel (with sth/sb)
with and at the same time as sth/sb else

data.chText: 新的学位课程和现有的证书课程将并行开设。

to be similar to sth; to happen at the same time as sth

data.chText: 他们的法律制度与我们的相似。
data.enText: Their legal system parallels our own.

data.chText: 在失业率上升的同时，轻度犯罪也跟着增长。
data.enText: The rise in unemployment is paralleled by an increase in petty crime.
to be as good as sth
a level of achievement that has never been paralleled

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 paralleling, paralleled

value.def: If something has a parallel, it is similar to something else, but exists or happens in a different place or at a different time. If it has no parallel or is without parallel, it is not similar to anything else.

example.ex: Readers familiar with English history will find a vague parallel to the suppression of the monasteries...
example.tran: 熟悉英国历史的读者会发现这与镇压修道院略有相似之处。

example.ex: It's an ecological disaster with no parallel anywhere else in the world.
example.tran: 这是一场在世界其他地方都没有出现过的生态灾难。

example.ex: ...an achievement without parallel in the modern era.

value.tran: （存在或发生在不同地点或时间的）相似之物，类似物

value.def: If there are parallels between two things, they are similar in some ways.

example.ex: Detailed study of folk music from a variety of countries reveals many close parallels...
example.tran: 仔细研究各国民间音乐后发现了许多非常相似之处。

example.ex: There are significant parallels with the 1980s...
example.tran: 与20世纪80年代有明显相似之处。

example.ex: Friends of the dead lawyer were quick to draw a parallel between the two murders.
example.tran: 遇害律师的朋友们很快发现了两起谋杀案之间的相似之处。

value.tran: （两者间的）近似之处，相似之处

value.def: If one thing parallels another, they happen at the same time or are similar, and often seem to be connected.

example.ex: Often there are emotional reasons paralleling the financial ones...
example.tran: 往往情感方面的原因和经济方面原因同时存在。

example.ex: The change in smoking is paralleled by a change in the incidence of lung cancer...
example.tran: 吸烟情况的变化与肺癌发病率的变化如影随形。

example.ex: His remarks paralleled those of the president.
example.tran: 他的言论和总统的如出一辙。

value.def: Parallel events or situations happen at the same time as one another, or are similar to one another.

example.ex: ...parallel talks between the two countries' Foreign Ministers...
example.tran: 两国外交部长同时进行的会谈

example.ex: Their instincts do not always run parallel with ours...
example.tran: 他们的本能并不总是和我们的相同。

example.ex: This is a real world, running parallel to our own.
example.tran: 这是个真实的世界，与我们的世界并存。

value.def: If two lines, two objects, or two lines of movement are parallel, they are the same distance apart along their whole length.

example.ex: ...seventy-two ships, drawn up in two parallel lines...
Farthing Lane's just above the High Street and parallel with it...
example.tran: 法辛巷刚好在大街的北面，与大街平行。

example.ex: This trail was roughly parallel to the border.
example.tran: 这条小路与边境线大致平行。

value.def: A parallel is an imaginary line round the earth that is parallel to the equator. Parallels are shown on maps.
Something that occurs in parallel with something else occurs at the same time as it.

example.ex: Davies has managed to pursue his diverse interests in parallel with his fast-moving career...
example.tran: 戴维斯在事业突飞猛进的同时并未放弃自己广泛的兴趣爱好。

example.ex: Progress on this issue must be made in parallel to any moves on the economic front.
example.tran: 这个问题上的进展应该和经济领域的进展同步。
